      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Congratulations to all concerned. The book reviews and the chronology that ran along the bottom of the pages provided fascinating insights into many of this century's most renowned authors. Unfortunately, there was nothing mentioned about John O'Hara.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Congratulations to all concerned. The book reviews and the chronology that ran along the bottom of the pages provided fascinating insights into many of this century's most renowned authors. Unfortunately, there was nothing mentioned about John O'Hara.</p>
        <p>Even if you didn't want to reprint a book review, you could have printed a short item about O'Hara in the chronology. Something along these lines, for 1934: '' 'Appointment in Samarra,' by John O'Hara, is published, the first of the author's many novels.''</p>
        <p>Richard de Thuin  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
